"You can set a default Incoterm rule to **automatically** populate the "
"Incoterm field on all newly created invoices and bills. "
"Under :menuselection:`Accounting/Invoicing --> Configuration --> Settings`, "
"scroll down to the :guilabel:`Customer Invoices` section, and select an "
"Incoterm in the :guilabel:`Default Incoterm` field."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto pravilo Incoterm lahko nastavite tako, da se polje Incoterm "
"**samodejno** izpolni na vseh novo ustvarjenih računih in predračunih. V "
"meniju :menuselection:`Računovodstvo/Izdajanje računov --> Nastavitve --> "
"Nastavitve` se pomaknite navzdol do odseka :guilabel:`Računi za stranke` in "
"v polju :guilabel:`Privzeti Incoterm` izberite Incoterm."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:3
msgid "Invoicing processes"
msgstr "Postopki izdajanja računov"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:5
msgid ""
"Depending on your business and the application you use, there are different "
"ways to automate the customer invoice creation in Odoo. Usually, draft "
"invoices are created by the system (with information coming from other "
"documents like sales order or contracts) and accountant just have to "
"validate draft invoices and send the invoices in batch (by regular mail or "
"email)."
msgstr ""
"Odvisno od vašega poslovanja in aplikacije, ki jo uporabljate, obstajajo "
"različni načini za avtomatizacijo ustvarjanja računov za stranke v Odoou. "
"Običajno sistem ustvari osnutke računov (s podatki iz drugih dokumentov, kot "
"so prodajni nalogi ali pogodbe), računovodja pa mora le potrditi osnutke "
"računov in jih poslati v paketu (po navadni pošti ali e-pošti)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:12
msgid ""
"Depending on your business, you may opt for one of the following way to "
"create draft invoices:"
msgstr ""
"Odvisno od vašega poslovanja se lahko odločite za enega od naslednjih "
"načinov ustvarjanja osnutkov računov:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:16
#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:205
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/mexico.rst:1524
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/new_zealand.rst:86
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/new_zealand.rst:94
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/switzerland.rst:130
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/switzerland.rst:132
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/switzerland.rst:134
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/switzerland.rst:136
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/turkiye.rst:225
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/turkiye.rst:233
msgid "Sales"
msgstr "Prodaja"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:21
msgid "Sales Order ‣ Invoice"
msgstr "Prodajni nalog → Račun"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:23
msgid ""
"In most companies, salespeople create quotations that become sales order "
"once they are validated. Then, draft invoices are created based on the sales "
"order. You have different options like:"
msgstr ""
"V večini podjetij prodajalci ustvarijo ponudbe, ki postanejo prodajni "
"nalogi, ko so potrjeni. Nato se na podlagi prodajnega naloga ustvarijo "
"osnutki računov. Na voljo so različne možnosti, kot so:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:27
msgid ""
"Invoice manually: use a button on the sale order to trigger the draft invoice"
msgstr ""
"Izdaj račun ročno: uporabite gumb na prodajnem nalogu za sprožitev osnutka "
"računa"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:30
msgid ""
"Invoice before delivery: invoice the full order before triggering the "
"delivery order"
msgstr ""
"Izdaj račun pred dobavo: izdaj račun za celotno naročilo, preden sprožiš "
"dobavnico"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:33
msgid "Invoice based on delivery order: see next section"
msgstr "Izdaj račun na podlagi dobavnice: glej naslednji oddelek"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:35
msgid ""
"Invoice before delivery is usually used by the eCommerce application when "
"the customer pays at the order and we deliver afterwards. (pre-paid)"
msgstr ""
"Izdaja računa pred dobavo se običajno uporablja v aplikaciji za e-trgovino, "
"ko stranka plača ob naročilu, mi pa dobavimo pozneje (predplačilo)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:39
msgid ""
"For most other use cases, it's recommended to invoice manually. It allows "
"the salesperson to trigger the invoice on demand with options: invoice the "
"whole order, invoice a percentage (advance), invoice some lines, invoice a "
"fixed advance."
msgstr ""
"Za večino drugih primerov uporabe je priporočljivo izdati račun ročno. To "
"prodajalcu omogoča, da sproži izdajo računa po potrebi z možnostmi: izdaj "
"račun za celotno naročilo, izdaj račun za odstotek (akontacija), izdaj račun "
"za nekatere postavke, izdaj račun za fiksno akontacijo."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:44
msgid "This process is good for both services and physical products."
msgstr "Ta postopek je primeren tako za storitve kot za fizične izdelke."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:50
msgid ""
"Invoices can also be generated from sales orders created in "
"the :doc:`Repairs app </applications/inventory_and_mrp/repairs>` for "
"invoicing after-sales services."
msgstr ""
"Račune je mogoče ustvariti tudi iz prodajnih nalogov, ustvarjenih v "
"aplikaciji :doc:`Popravila </applications/inventory_and_mrp/repairs>`, za "
"izdajanje računov za poprodajne storitve."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:55
msgid "Sales Order ‣ Delivery Order ‣ Invoice"
msgstr "Prodajni nalog → Dobavnica → Račun"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:57
msgid ""
"Retailers and eCommerce usually invoice based on delivery orders, instead of "
"sales order. This approach is suitable for businesses where the quantities "
"you deliver may differs from the ordered quantities: foods (invoice based on "
"actual Kg)."
msgstr ""
"Trgovci na drobno in e-trgovina običajno izdajajo račune na podlagi "
"dobavnic, namesto na podlagi prodajnih nalogov. Ta pristop je primeren za "
"podjetja, kjer se lahko dobavljene količine razlikujejo od naročenih "
"količin: hrana (izdaja računa na podlagi dejanskih kg)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:62
msgid ""
"This way, if you deliver a partial order, you only invoice for what you "
"really delivered. If you do back orders (deliver partially and the rest "
"later), the customer will receive two invoices, one for each delivery order."
msgstr ""
"Na ta način, če dobavite delno naročilo, izdaste račun samo za tisto, kar "
"ste dejansko dobavili. Če izvajate naknadne dobave (delna dobava in "
"preostanek pozneje), bo stranka prejela dva računa, po enega za vsako "
"dobavnico."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:68
msgid ":doc:`/applications/sales/sales/invoicing/invoicing_policy`"
msgstr ":doc:`/applications/sales/sales/invoicing/invoicing_policy`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:71
msgid "eCommerce Order ‣ Invoice"
msgstr "Naročilo v e-trgovini → Račun"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:73
msgid ""
"An eCommerce order will also trigger the creation of the order when it is "
"fully paid. If you allow paying orders by check or wire transfer, Odoo only "
"creates an order and the invoice will be triggered once the payment is "
"received."
msgstr ""
"Naročilo v e-trgovini bo sprožilo tudi ustvarjanje naročila, ko je v celoti "
"plačano. Če dovolite plačilo naročil s čekom ali bančnim nakazilom, Odoo "
"ustvari samo naročilo, račun pa bo sprožen, ko je plačilo prejeto."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:79
msgid "Contracts"
msgstr "Pogodbe"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:82
msgid "Regular Contracts ‣ Invoices"
msgstr "Redne pogodbe → Računi"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:84
msgid ""
"If you use contracts, you can trigger invoice based on time and material "
"spent, expenses or fixed lines of services/products. Every month, the "
"salesperson will trigger invoice based on activities on the contract."
msgstr ""
"Če uporabljate pogodbe, lahko sprožite izdajo računa na podlagi porabljenega "
"časa in materiala, stroškov ali fiksnih postavk storitev/izdelkov. Vsak "
"mesec bo prodajalec sprožil izdajo računa na podlagi aktivnosti na pogodbi."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:88
msgid "Activities can be:"
msgstr "Aktivnosti so lahko:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:90
msgid ""
"fixed products/services, coming from a sale order linked to this contract"
msgstr ""
"fiksni izdelki/storitve, ki izhajajo iz prodajnega naloga, povezanega s to "
"pogodbo"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:91
msgid "materials purchased (that you will re-invoice)"
msgstr "kupljeni materiali (ki jih boste znova zaračunali)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:92
msgid "time and material based on timesheets or purchases (subcontracting)"
msgstr "čas in material na podlagi časovnic ali nakupov (podizvajanje)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:93
msgid ""
"expenses like travel and accommodation that you re-invoice to the customer"
msgstr ""
"stroški, kot so potovanje in nastanitev, ki jih znova zaračunate stranki"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:95
msgid ""
"You can invoice at the end of the contract or trigger intermediate invoices. "
"This approach is used by services companies that invoice mostly based on "
"time and material. For services companies that invoice on fix price, they "
"use a regular sales order."
msgstr ""
"Lahko izdate račun ob koncu pogodbe ali sprožite vmesne račune. Ta pristop "
"uporabljajo storitvena podjetja, ki zaračunavajo predvsem na podlagi "
"porabljenega časa in materiala. Storitvena podjetja, ki zaračunavajo po "
"fiksni ceni, uporabljajo običajen prodajni nalog."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:101
msgid ":doc:`/applications/sales/sales/invoicing/time_materials`"
msgstr ":doc:`/applications/sales/sales/invoicing/time_materials`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:103
msgid ":doc:`/applications/sales/sales/invoicing/milestone`"
msgstr ":doc:`/applications/sales/sales/invoicing/milestone`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:106
msgid "Recurring Contracts ‣ Invoices"
msgstr "Ponavljajoče se pogodbe ‣ Računi"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:108
msgid ""
"For subscriptions, an invoice is triggered periodically, automatically. The "
"frequency of the invoicing and the services/products invoiced are defined on "
"the contract."
msgstr ""
"Pri naročninah se račun sproži periodično, samodejno. Pogostost izdajanja "
"računov ter zaračunane storitve/izdelki so določeni v pogodbi."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:113
msgid ":doc:`/applications/sales/subscriptions`"
msgstr ":doc:`/applications/sales/subscriptions`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:116
msgid "Others"
msgstr "Ostali"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:119
msgid "Creating an invoice manually"
msgstr "Ročno ustvarjanje računa"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:121
msgid ""
"Users can also create invoices manually without using contracts or a sales "
"order. It's a recommended approach if you do not need to manage the sales "
"process (quotations), or the delivery of the products or services."
msgstr ""
"Uporabniki lahko ustvarijo račune tudi ročno, brez uporabe pogodb ali "
"prodajnega naloga. To je priporočljiv pristop, če vam ni treba upravljati "
"prodajnega procesa (ponudbe) ali dostave izdelkov ali storitev."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:126
msgid ""
"Even if you generate the invoice from a sales order, you may need to create "
"invoices manually in exceptional use cases:"
msgstr ""
"Tudi če račun ustvarite iz prodajnega naloga, boste morda morali v izjemnih "
"primerih račune ustvariti ročno:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:129
msgid "if you need to create a refund"
msgstr "če morate ustvariti dobropis"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:131
msgid "If you need to give a discount"
msgstr "Če morate dati popust"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:133
msgid "if you need to change an invoice created from a sales order"
msgstr "če morate spremeniti račun, ustvarjen iz prodajnega naloga"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:135
msgid "if you need to invoice something not related to your core business"
msgstr "če morate zaračunati nekaj, kar ni povezano z vašo osnovno dejavnostjo"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:138
msgid "Resequencing of the invoices"
msgstr "Prerazporeditev računov"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:140
msgid ""
"It remains possible to resequence the invoices but with some restrictions:"
msgstr ""
"Še vedno je mogoče preštevilčiti račune, vendar z določenimi omejitvami:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:142
msgid "The feature does not work when entries are previous to a lock date."
msgstr "Funkcija ne deluje, če so vnosi pred datumom zaklepa."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:143
msgid ""
"The feature does not work if the sequence is inconsistent with the month of "
"the entry."
msgstr "Funkcija ne deluje, če zaporednost ni skladna z mesecem vnosa."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:144
msgid "It does not work if the sequence leads to a duplicate."
msgstr "Ne deluje, če zaporednost vodi do podvojitve."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:145
msgid "The order of the invoice remains unchanged."
msgstr "Vrstni red računa ostaja nespremenjen."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:146
msgid ""
"It is useful for people who use a numbering from another software and who "
"want to continue the current year without starting over from the beginning."
msgstr ""
"To je uporabno za tiste, ki uporabljajo številčenje iz druge programske "
"opreme in želijo nadaljevati tekoče leto, ne da bi začeli znova od začetka."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:150
msgid "Invoice digitization with optical character recognition (OCR)"
msgstr "Digitalizacija računov z optičnim prepoznavanjem znakov (OCR)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:152
msgid ""
"**Invoice digitization** is the process of automatically encoding "
"traditional paper invoices into invoices forms in your accounting."
msgstr ""
"**Digitalizacija računov** je postopek samodejnega kodiranja tradicionalnih "
"papirnatih računov v obrazce računov v vašem računovodstvu."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:155
msgid ""
"Odoo uses OCR and artificial intelligence technologies to recognize the "
"content of the documents. Vendor bills and customer invoices forms are "
"automatically created and populated based on scanned invoices."
msgstr ""
"Odoo uporablja tehnologije OCR in umetne inteligence za prepoznavanje "
"vsebine dokumentov. Obrazci dobaviteljevih računov in računov za stranke se "
"samodejno ustvarijo in izpolnijo na podlagi skeniranih računov."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/overview.rst:160
msgid ""
":doc:`/applications/finance/accounting/vendor_bills/invoice_digitization`"
msgstr ""
":doc:`/applications/finance/accounting/vendor_bills/invoice_digitization`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:3
msgid "Payment terms and installment plans"
msgstr "Plačilni pogoji in načrti obrokov"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:5
msgid ""
"**Payment terms** specify all the conditions of a sale's payment to help "
"ensure customers pay their invoices correctly and on time."
msgstr ""
"**Plačilni pogoji** določajo vse pogoje plačila prodaje, da pomagajo "
"zagotoviti, da stranke svoje račune plačajo pravilno in pravočasno."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:8
msgid ""
"Payment terms are generally defined on documents such as sales orders, "
"customer invoices, and vendor bills. Payment terms cover:"
msgstr ""
"Plačilni pogoji so na splošno opredeljeni v dokumentih, kot so prodajni "
"nalogi, računi za stranke in dobaviteljevi računi. Plačilni pogoji zajemajo:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:11
msgid "The due date(s)"
msgstr "Rok(e) plačila"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:12
msgid "Early payment discounts"
msgstr "Popusti za predčasno plačilo"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:13
msgid "Any other conditions on the payment"
msgstr "Vsi drugi pogoji glede plačila"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:15
msgid ""
"An **installment plan** allows the customers to pay an invoice in parts, "
"with the amounts and payment dates defined beforehand by the seller."
msgstr ""
"**Načrt obrokov** strankam omogoča, da plačajo račun v delih, pri čemer so "
"zneske in datume plačil vnaprej določil prodajalec."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:19
msgid "Immediate Payment"
msgstr "Takojšnje plačilo"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:20
msgid "The full payment is due on the day of the invoice's issuance."
msgstr "Celotno plačilo zapade na dan izdaje računa."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:21
msgid "15 Days (or Net 15)"
msgstr "15 dni (ali Neto 15)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:22
msgid "The full payment is due 15 days after the invoice date."
msgstr "Celotno plačilo zapade 15 dni po datumu računa."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:23
msgid "21 MFI"
msgstr "21 MFI"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:24
msgid ""
"The full payment is due by the 21st of the month following the invoice date."
msgstr ""
"Celotno plačilo je potrebno opraviti do 21. dne v mesecu, ki sledi datumu "
"izdaje računa."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:26
msgid "30% Advance End of Following Month"
msgstr "30% avans ob koncu naslednjega meseca"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:26
msgid ""
"30% is due on the day of the invoice's issuance. The remaining balance is "
"due at the end of the following month."
msgstr ""
"30 % je potrebno plačati na dan izdaje računa. Preostali znesek je potrebno "
"plačati do konca naslednjega meseca."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:29
msgid "2% 10, Net 30 EOM"
msgstr "2% 10, Neto 30 EOM"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:29
msgid ""
"A 2% :doc:`cash discount <cash_discounts>` if the payment is received within "
"ten days. Otherwise, the full payment is due at the end of the month "
"following the invoice date."
msgstr ""
"2-odstotni :doc:`popust za plačilo v gotovin <cash_discounts>`, če je "
"plačilo prejeto v desetih dneh. Sicer je celotno plačilo potrebno opraviti "
"do konca meseca, ki sledi datumu izdaje računa."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:33
msgid ""
"Payment terms are not to be confused with :doc:`down payment invoices </"
"applications/sales/sales/invoicing/down_payment>`. If, for a specific order, "
"you issue multiple invoices to your customer, that is neither a payment term "
"nor an installment plan but an invoicing policy."
msgstr ""
"Plačilnih pogojev ne smemo zamenjati z :doc:`računi za avans </applications/"
"sales/sales/invoicing/down_payment>`. Če za določeno naročilo svojemu "
"stranki izdaste več računov, to ni niti plačilni pogoj niti načrt obročnega "
"plačevanja, temveč politika izdajanja računov."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:37
msgid ""
"This page is about the *payment terms* feature, not :doc:`terms & conditions "
"<terms_conditions>`, which can be used to declare contractual obligations "
"regarding content use, return policies, and other policies surrounding the "
"sale of goods and services."
msgstr ""
"Ta stran govori o funkciji *plačilnih pogojev*, ne o :doc:`splošnih pogojih "
"<terms_conditions>`, ki se lahko uporabijo za navedbo pogodbenih obveznosti "
"glede uporabe vsebine, politike vračil in drugih politik, povezanih s "
"prodajo blaga in storitev."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:42
msgid ""
"`Odoo Tutorials: payment terms <https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/payment-"
"terms-1679>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Priročniki Odoo: plačilni pogoji <https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/payment-"
"terms-1679>`_"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:43
msgid ":doc:`cash_discounts`"
msgstr ":doc:`cash_discounts`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:50
msgid "To create new payment terms, follow these steps:"
msgstr "Za ustvarjanje novih plačilnih pogojev upoštevajte naslednje korake:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:52
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration --> Payment Terms` and "
"click on :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"Pojdite na :menuselection:`Računovodstvo --> Konfiguracija --> Plačilni "
"pogoji` in kliknite na :guilabel:`Novo`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:54
msgid ""
"Enter a name in the :guilabel:`Payment Terms` field. This field is the name "
"displayed both internally and on sales orders."
msgstr ""
"V polje :guilabel:`Plačilni pogoji` vnesite ime. To polje je ime, ki se "
"prikazuje tako interno kot na prodajnih nalogih."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:56
msgid ""
"Tick the :guilabel:`Early Discount` checkbox and fill out the discount "
"percentage, discount days, and :ref:`tax reduction <cash-discounts/tax-"
"reductions>` fields to add a :doc:`cash discount <cash_discounts>`, if "
"desired."
msgstr ""
"Potrdite potrditveno polje :guilabel:`Zgodnji popust` in izpolnite polja za "
"odstotek popusta, dneve popusta in :ref:`zmanjšanje davka <cash-discounts/"
"tax-reductions>`, da dodate :doc:`popust za plačilo v gotovini "
"<cash_discounts>`, če je to zahtevano."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:59
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Due Terms` section, add a set of rules (terms) to define "
"what needs to be paid and by which due date(s). Defining terms automatically "
"calculates the payments' due date(s). This is particularly helpful for "
"managing **installment plans** (:dfn:`payment terms with multiple terms`)."
msgstr ""
"V razdelku :guilabel:`Roki dospelosti` dodajte niz pravil (pogojev), ki "
"določajo, kaj je potrebno plačati in do katerih datumov dospelosti. "
"Določanje pogojev samodejno izračuna datume dospelosti plačil. To je posebej "
"koristno za upravljanje **načrtov obročnega plačevanja** (:dfn:`plačilni "
"pogoji z več pogoji`)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:64
msgid ""
"To add a term, click on :guilabel:`Add a line`, define the discount's value "
"and type in the :guilabel:`Due` fields, then fill out the :guilabel:`After` "
"fields to determine the due date."
msgstr ""
"Za dodajanje pogoja kliknite na :guilabel:`Dodaj vrstico`, določite vrednost "
"in vrsto popusta v poljih :guilabel:`Dospelo`, nato izpolnite polja "
":guilabel:`Po`, da določite datum dospelosti."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:68
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Days end of the month on the` option allows you to add "
"a :ref:`buffer period <accounting/payment-terms/buffer>` so that an invoice "
"registered at the end of the month isn't due at the beginning of the month "
"that immediately follows."
msgstr ""
"Možnost :guilabel:`Dni konec meseca na` vam omogoča, da dodate "
":ref:`zaščitno obdobje <accounting/payment-terms/buffer>`, tako da račun, "
"registriran ob koncu meseca, ne zapade v plačilo na začetku meseca, ki "
"neposredno sledi."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:72
msgid ""
"Enter the text to be displayed on the document (sales order, invoice, etc.) "
"in the gray textbox in the :guilabel:`Preview` column."
msgstr ""
"Vnesite besedilo, ki naj se prikazuje na dokumentu (prodajni nalog, račun "
"itd.) v sivo tekstovno polje v stolpcu :guilabel:`Predogled`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:74
msgid ""
"Tick the :guilabel:`Show installment dates` checkbox to display a breakdown "
"of each payment and its due date on the invoice report, if desired."
msgstr ""
"Potrdite potrditveno polje :guilabel:`Prikaži datume obročnega plačevanja`, "
"da se na poročilu računa prikazuje razpis vsakega plačila in njegovega "
"datuma dospelosti, če je to zahtevano."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:78
msgid ""
"To instead specify a number of days *before the end of the month*, use a "
"negative value in the :guilabel:`After` field."
msgstr ""
"Namesto tega določite število dni *pred koncem meseca* tako, da v polje "
":guilabel:`Po` vnesete negativno vrednost."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:81
msgid ""
"To test that your payment terms are configured correctly, enter an invoice "
"date on the :guilabel:`Example` line to generate the payments that would be "
"due and their due dates using these payment terms."
msgstr ""
"Za preizkus, ali so vaši plačilni pogoji pravilno konfigurirani, vnesite "
"datum izdaje računa v vrstico :guilabel:`Primer`, da ustvarite plačila, ki "
"bi zapadla v plačilo, in njihove datume dospelosti z uporabo teh plačilnih "
"pogojev."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:86
msgid "Terms are computed in the order of their due dates."
msgstr "Pogoji se izračunajo po vrstnem redu njihovih rokov plačila."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:89
msgid ""
"In the following example, 30% is due on the day of issuance, and the "
"remaining 70% is due at the end of the following month."
msgstr ""
"V naslednjem primeru je 30 % dolgovanega na dan izdaje, preostalih 70 % pa "
"je dolgovanega ob koncu naslednjega meseca."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:0
msgid ""
"Example of Payment Terms. The first line is the 30% due immediately. The "
"second line is\n"
"the remaining 70% due at the end of the following month."
msgstr ""
"Primer plačilnih pogojev. Prva vrstica je 30 %, dolgovanega takoj. Druga "
"vrstica je\n"
"preostalih 70 %, dolgovanega ob koncu naslednjega meseca."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:99
msgid "End of the month buffer"
msgstr "Dodaten čas na koncu meseca"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:101
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Days end of the month on the` option allows users to add a "
"buffer period so that an invoice registered at the end of the month isn't "
"due at the beginning of the month that immediately follows."
msgstr ""
"Možnost :guilabel:`Dni konec meseca na` uporabnikom omogoča dodajanje "
"dodatnega časovnega obdobja, tako da račun, registriran konec meseca, ni "
"takoj dospel v začetku meseca, ki neposredno sledi."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:105
msgid ""
"When using this option, Odoo calculates the due date by taking the invoice "
"date, adding the integer in the :guilabel:`After` field, going to the end of "
"the resulting month, and then adding the integer from the :guilabel:`Days on "
"the next month` field."
msgstr ""
"Pri uporabi te možnosti Odoo izračuna rok plačila tako, da vzame datum "
"računa, prišteje celo število iz polja :guilabel:`Po`, gre na konec "
"pridobljenega meseca in nato prišteje celo število iz polja :guilabel:`Dni "
"naslednjega meseca`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:110
msgid ""
"For example, take two invoices, one dated 5 March and the other dated 28 "
"March. Both use the same payment terms with a single :guilabel:`Due Terms` "
"line for 100% of the due amount, due `5` :guilabel:`Days end of the month on "
"the` `1`."
msgstr ""
"Na primer, vzemimo dva računa, enega z datumom 5. marec in drugega z datumom "
"28. marec. Oba uporabljata enake plačilne pogoje z eno vrstico "
":guilabel:`Pogoji za dospelost` za 100 % dolgovanega zneska, dospelega `5` "
":guilabel:`Dni konec meseca na` `1`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:114
msgid ""
"For the invoice dated 5 March, the due date is computed as **1 April** with "
"the following calculations:"
msgstr ""
"Za račun z datumom 5. marec se rok plačila izračuna kot **1. april** z "
"naslednjimi izračuni:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:117
msgid "5 March + 5 days = 10 March"
msgstr "5. marec + 5 dni = 10. marec"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:118
msgid "10 March + end of the month = 31 March"
msgstr "10. marec + konec meseca = 31. marec"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:119
msgid "31 March + on the 1 = 1 April"
msgstr "31. marec + na 1. = 1. april"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:122
msgid ""
"For the invoice dated 28 March, the due date is computed as **1 May** with "
"the following calculations:"
msgstr ""
"Za račun z datumom 28. marec se rok plačila izračuna kot **1. maj** z "
"naslednjimi izračuni:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:125
msgid "28 March + 5 days = 2 April"
msgstr "28. marec + 5 dni = 2. april"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:126
msgid "2 April + end of the month = 30 April"
msgstr "2. april + konec meseca = 30. april"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:127
msgid "30 April + on the 1 = 1 May"
msgstr "30. april + na 1. = 1. maj"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:132
msgid "Using payment terms"
msgstr "Uporaba plačilnih pogojev"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:134
msgid ""
"Payment terms can be defined using the :guilabel:`Payment Terms` field on:"
msgstr ""
"Plačilne pogoje lahko določite z uporabo polja :guilabel:`Plačilni pogoji` "
"na:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:136
msgid ""
"**Contacts:** To automatically set default payment terms on a contact's new "
"sales orders, invoices, and bills. This can be modified in the contact form, "
"under the :guilabel:`Sales & Purchase` tab."
msgstr ""
"**Stiki:** Za samodejno nastavitev privzetih plačilnih pogojev na novih "
"prodajnih nalogih, računih in prejemkih stika. To lahko spremenite v obrazcu "
"stika, pod zavihkom :guilabel:`Prodaja in nakup`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:139
msgid ""
"**Quotations/Sales Orders:** To set specific payment terms automatically on "
"all invoices generated from a quotation or sales order."
msgstr ""
"**Ponudbe/prodajni nalogi:** Za nastavitev določenih plačilnih pogojev "
"samodejno na vseh računih, ustvarjenih iz ponudbe ali prodajnega naloga."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:142
msgid ""
"Payment terms can be defined using the :guilabel:`Due Date` field, with "
"the :guilabel:`Terms` drop-down list on:"
msgstr ""
"Plačilne pogoje lahko določite z uporabo polja :guilabel:`Rok plačila` s "
"spustnim seznamom :guilabel:`Pogoji` na:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:145
msgid "**Customer invoices:** To set specific payment terms on an invoice."
msgstr "**Računi strank:** Za določitev posebnih plačilnih pogojev na računu."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:146
msgid "**Vendor bills:** To set specific payment terms on a bill."
msgstr ""
"**Dobaviteljski računi:** Za določitev posebnih plačilnih pogojev na računu."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:149
msgid ""
"Setting payment terms on a vendor bill is mostly useful for managing vendor "
"terms with multiple installments or cash discounts. Otherwise, manually "
"setting the **due date** is enough. If payment terms are already defined, "
"empty the field to select a date."
msgstr ""
"Določanje plačilnih pogojev na dobaviteljskem računu je večinoma koristno za "
"upravljanje pogojev dobavitelja z več obrokov ali gotovinskimi popusti. "
"Sicer je dovolj ročno nastaviti **datum zapadlosti**. Če so plačilni pogoji "
"že določeni, izpraznite polje, da izberete datum."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:158
msgid ""
"Invoices with specific payment terms generate different *journal entries*, "
"with one *journal item* for every computed *due date*."
msgstr ""
"Računi s posebnimi plačilnimi pogoji ustvarijo različne *knjižne vnose* z "
"enim *knjižnim postavko* za vsak izračunan *datum zapadlosti*."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:161
msgid ""
"This makes for easier :doc:`follow-ups </applications/finance/accounting/"
"payments/follow_up>` and :doc:`reconciliation </applications/finance/"
"accounting/bank/reconciliation>` since Odoo takes each due date into "
"account, rather than just the balance due date. It also helps to get an "
"accurate :ref:`aged receivable report <accounting/invoices/aging-report>`."
msgstr ""
"To olajša :doc:`spremljanje </applications/finance/accounting/payments/"
"follow_up>` in :doc:`uskladitev </applications/finance/accounting/bank/"
"reconciliation>`, saj Odoo upošteva vsak datum zapadlosti, namesto samo "
"datum zapadlosti stanja. Pomaga tudi pri pridobivanju natančnega "
":ref:`poročila o starostni analizi terjatev <accounting/invoices/aging-"
"report>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:None
msgid ""
"The amount debited to the account receivable is split into two journal items "
"with\n"
"distinct due dates"
msgstr ""
"Znesek, bremenit na račun terjatev, je razdeljen na dve knjižni postavki z\n"
"ločenima datumoma zapadlosti"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/customer_invoices/payment_terms.rst:171
msgid ""
"In this example, an invoice of $1000 has been issued with the following "
"payment terms: *30% is due on the day of issuance, and the remaining 70% is "
"due at the end of the following month.*"
msgstr ""
"V tem primeru je bil izdan račun za 1000 $ z naslednjimi plačilnimi pogoji: "
"*30 % zapade na dan izdaje, preostalih 70 % pa zapade na koncu naslednjega "
"meseca.*"

