msgstr "Nastavite, kako se davek prikazuje strankam"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:239
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/australia.rst:78
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/australia.rst:106
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/new_zealand.rst:81
msgid "Label on invoices"
msgstr "Oznaka na računih"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:241
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Label on Invoices` appears on invoice lines in invoice PDFs "
"and on the customer portal."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Oznaka na računih` se prikaže na vrsticah računov v PDF-jih "
"računov in na portalu za stranke."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid ""
"The Label on Invoice shows on the invoice line when viewed in the customer "
"portal."
msgstr ""
"Oznaka na računu se prikaže v vrstici računa pri ogledu na portalu za "
"stranke."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:250
msgid "Tax group"
msgstr "Davčna skupina"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:252
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Tax Group` is shown in the totals section of the invoice, in "
"invoice PDFs and on the customer portal. Multiple taxes that belong to the "
"same tax group are aggregated together into a single tax amount."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Davčna skupina` je prikazana v razdelku vsot računa, v PDF-jih "
"računov in na portalu za stranke. Več davkov, ki pripadajo isti davčni "
"skupini, se združi v en sam davčni znesek."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid ""
"The Tax Group shows in the totals section when viewed in the customer portal."
msgstr ""
"Davčna skupina se prikaže v razdelku vsot pri ogledu na portalu za stranke."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:262
msgid "Configure how tax journal items are created"
msgstr "Nastavite, kako se ustvarijo vnosi v davčnem dnevniku"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:264
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Distribution for Invoices` and :guilabel:`Distribution for "
"Refunds` sections control the generation of tax payable journal items in "
"invoices and credit notes, respectively. They also determine which :ref:`tax "
"grids <accounting/tax-returns/tax-grids>` are set on invoice lines when this "
"tax is applied."
msgstr ""
"Razdelka :guilabel:`Porazdelitev za račune` in :guilabel:`Porazdelitev za "
"dobropise` nadzorujeta ustvarjanje vnosov davčnih obveznosti v računih "
"oziroma dobropisih. Določata tudi, katere :ref:`davčne mreže <accounting/tax-"
"returns/tax-grids>` so nastavljene na vrsticah računov, ko se uporabi ta "
"davek."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:269
msgid ""
"Each of these sections should contain one :guilabel:`Base` line, one or "
"more :guilabel:`% of tax` lines amounting to 100% (e.g. one 100% line, or "
"two 50% lines), and optionally, one or more :guilabel:`% of tax` lines "
"amounting to -100.00%."
msgstr ""
"Vsak od teh razdelkov mora vsebovati eno vrstico :guilabel:`Osnova`, eno ali "
"več vrstic :guilabel:`% davka`, ki znašajo skupaj 100 % (npr. ena vrstica "
"100 % ali dve vrstici 50 %), in po potrebi eno ali več vrstic :guilabel:`% "
"davka`, ki znašajo skupaj -100,00 %."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:273
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Base` line can have one or more :guilabel:`Tax Grids` set, "
"which are added to the invoice line on which the tax is applied."
msgstr ""
"Vrstica :guilabel:`Osnova` ima lahko nastavljeno eno ali več "
":guilabel:`Davčnih mrež`, ki se dodajo vrstici računa, na katero se uporabi "
"davek."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:276
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`% of tax` lines control the creation of tax payable journal "
"items. The tax amount is distributed according to the percentages on these "
"lines, and each line is then used as a template to create a tax payable "
"journal item with the same :guilabel:`Account` and :guilabel:`Tax Grids`. If "
"the :guilabel:`Account` is not specified, it defaults to the account of the "
"original invoice line on which the tax is applied."
msgstr ""
"Vrstice :guilabel:`% davka` nadzorujejo ustvarjanje vnosov davčnih "
"obveznosti. Davčni znesek se razdeli glede na odstotke v teh vrsticah in "
"vsaka vrstica se nato uporabi kot predloga za ustvarjanje vnosa davčne "
"obveznosti z enakim :guilabel:`Kontom` in :guilabel:`Davčnimi mrežami`. Če "
":guilabel:`Konto` ni določen, se privzeto uporabi konto prvotne vrstice "
"računa, na katero se uporabi davek."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:282
msgid "Typical cases include:"
msgstr "Tipični primeri vključujejo:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:284
msgid ""
"one :guilabel:`100% of tax` line: this is the most common case where the tax "
"amount should appear on a single tax payable journal item."
msgstr ""
"ena vrstica :guilabel:`100 % davka`: to je najpogostejši primer, ko mora "
"biti davčni znesek prikazan na enem samem vnosu davčne obveznosti."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:286
msgid ""
"one :guilabel:`100% of tax` and one :guilabel:`-100% of tax` line: this is "
"appropriate if the tax simultaneously generates both a tax debit and a tax "
"credit which cancel each other out (e.g. EU intra-community reverse-charge "
"VAT)."
msgstr ""
"ena vrstica :guilabel:`100 % davka` in ena vrstica :guilabel:`-100 % davka`: "
"to je primerno, če davek hkrati ustvari tako davčni dolg kot davčni "
"dobropis, ki se medsebojno izničita (npr. EU obratno zadolženi DDV za "
"trgovino znotraj Skupnosti)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:289
msgid ""
"one :guilabel:`50% of tax` line that specifies a tax payable account and "
"another :guilabel:`50% of tax` line that does not specify an account: this "
"is appropriate for partially deductible purchase VAT, where part of the tax "
"must be considered an expense rather than a tax credit asset that can offset "
"tax liability."
msgstr ""
"ena vrstica :guilabel:`50 % davka`, ki določa konto davčne obveznosti, in "
"druga vrstica :guilabel:`50 % davka`, ki ne določa konta: to je primerno za "
"delno odbitni DDV pri nabavi, kjer mora biti del davka obravnavan kot "
"strošek in ne kot sredstvo davčnega dobropisa, ki lahko poravna davčno "
"obveznost."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid "The Distribution for Invoices of a 21% VAT tax."
msgstr "Porazdelitev za račune za 21 % DDV."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid "The Distribution for Refunds of a 21% VAT tax."
msgstr "Porazdelitev za dobropise za 21 % DDV."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:303
#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:388
#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/fiscal_positions.rst:35
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/australia.rst:61
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/new_zealand.rst:65
msgid "Tax mapping"
msgstr "Preslikovanje davkov"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:305
msgid ""
"Taxes can be combined with :doc:`fiscal positions <taxes/fiscal_positions>` "
"to map taxes to each other so that the correct tax is applied based on the "
"customer's or vendor's location and business type."
msgstr ""
"Davke je mogoče kombinirati s :doc:`fiskalnimi položaji <taxes/"
"fiscal_positions>`, da se davki preslikajo drug v drugega, tako da se "
"uporabi pravilni davek glede na lokacijo in vrsto poslovanja stranke ali "
"dobavitelja."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:309
msgid ""
"When configuring a tax, leave the :guilabel:`Fiscal Position` field blank to "
"make the tax immediately available across all fiscal positions, or select "
"specific fiscal positions where this tax should be used to replace other "
"taxes with it. If one or more fiscal positions are selected, use "
"the :guilabel:`Replaces` field to select all of the taxes that this tax "
"should replace for the selected fiscal position(s)."
msgstr ""
"Pri nastavitvi davka pustite polje :guilabel:`Davčni položaj` prazno, da bo "
"davek takoj na voljo v vseh davčnih položajih, ali izberite določene davčne "
"položaje, kjer naj se ta davek uporabi za zamenjavo drugih davkov. Če je "
"izbran en ali več davčnih položajev, uporabite polje :guilabel:`Nadomešča`, "
"da izberete vse davke, ki naj jih ta davek nadomesti za izbrane davčne "
"položaje."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:315
msgid ""
"To replace one tax with multiple other taxes, configure each of the "
"replacement taxes to replace the default product tax."
msgstr ""
"Za zamenjavo enega davka z več drugimi davki konfigurirajte vsak nadomestni "
"davek tako, da nadomesti privzeti davek na izdelku."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:319
msgid ""
"As a sales tax, the :guilabel:`0% Exports` tax applies to quotations, sales "
"orders, and invoices that use the :guilabel:`Foreign Trade` fiscal position. "
"On those records, any time that the :guilabel:`15%` tax would be used, "
"the :guilabel:`0% Exports` tax is used instead."
msgstr ""
"Kot prometni davek se davek :guilabel:`0% izvoz` uporablja za ponudbe, "
"prodajne naloge in račune, ki uporabljajo fiskalni položaj "
":guilabel:`Zunanja trgovina`. Pri teh zapisih se, kadarkoli bi se uporabil "
"davek :guilabel:`15%`, namesto tega uporabi davek :guilabel:`0% izvoz`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:0
msgid "The **0% Exports** tax record"
msgstr "Zapis davka **0% izvoz**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:327
msgid ""
"Since the first fiscal position in the sequence is considered the company's "
"default, the taxes set on products are expected to be used with that fiscal "
"position, so the :guilabel:`Replaces` field is not displayed on it."
msgstr ""
"Ker je prvi fiskalni položaj v zaporedju privzeti fiskalni položaj podjetja, "
"se pričakuje, da bodo davki, nastavljeni na izdelkih, uporabljeni s tem "
"fiskalnim položajem, zato polje :guilabel:`Nadomešča` ni prikazano."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:332
msgid ""
"To more easily view which taxes are replaced, use the :icon:`oi-settings-"
"adjust` :guilabel:`adjust settings` in the taxes list view and display "
"the :guilabel:`Replaces` field."
msgstr ""
"Za lažji pregled, kateri davki so nadomeščeni, uporabite :icon:`oi-settings-"
"adjust` :guilabel:`nastavitve prikaza` v seznamskem pogledu davkov in "
"prikažite polje :guilabel:`Nadomešča`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:0
msgid "The **Replaces** field shown in the list view"
msgstr "Polje **Nadomešča**, prikazano v seznamskem pogledu"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:339
msgid ""
"Tax mapping only works with :ref:`active <taxes/list_activation>` taxes."
msgstr ""
"Preslikava davkov deluje samo z :ref:`aktivnimi <taxes/list_activation>` "
"davki."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:342
msgid "Extra taxes"
msgstr "Dodatni davki"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:344
msgid ""
"\"Extra taxes\" is a broad term referring to additional taxes beyond the "
"standard or basic taxes imposed by governments. These extra taxes can be "
"**luxury** taxes, **environmental** taxes, **import** or **export duties** "
"taxes, etc."
msgstr ""
"\"Dodatni davki\" je širok izraz, ki se nanaša na dodatne davke poleg "
"standardnih ali osnovnih davkov, ki jih nalagajo vlade. Ti dodatni davki so "
"lahko davki na **luksuz**, **okoljski** davki, **uvozne** ali **izvozne "
"carine**, itd."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:349
msgid ""
"The method to compute these taxes varies across different countries. We "
"recommend consulting your country's regulations to understand how to "
"calculate them for your business."
msgstr ""
"Metoda za izračun teh davkov se razlikuje med državami. Priporočamo, da se "
"posvetujete s predpisi svoje države, da razumete, kako jih izračunati za "
"svoje podjetje."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:352
msgid ""
"To compute an extra tax in Odoo, :ref:`create a tax <taxes/configuration>`, "
"enter a tax name, select a :ref:`Tax Computation <taxes/configuration>`, set "
"an :guilabel:`Amount`, and in the :guilabel:`Advanced Options` tab, "
"enable :guilabel:`Affect Base of Subsequent Taxes`. Then, drag and drop the "
"taxes in the :ref:`order they should be computed <taxes/base-subsequent>`."
msgstr ""
"Za izračun dodatnega davka v Odoo :ref:`ustvarite davek <taxes/configuration>"
"`, vnesite ime davka, izberite :ref:`Izračun davka <taxes/configuration>`, "
"nastavite :guilabel:`Znesek` in v zavihku :guilabel:`Napredne možnosti` "
"omogočite :guilabel:`Vpliva na osnovo naslednjih davkov`. Nato povlecite in "
"spustite davke v :ref:`vrstnem redu, v katerem naj se izračunajo <taxes/base-"
"subsequent>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:358
msgid ""
"In Belgium, the formula to compute an environmental tax is: `(product price "
"+ environmental tax) x sales tax`. Therefore, our environmental tax has to "
"come *before* the sales tax in the computation sequence."
msgstr ""
"V Belgiji je formula za izračun okoljskega davka: `(cena izdelka + okoljski "
"davek) x davek od prodaje`. Zato mora naš okoljski davek priti *pred* davkom "
"od prodaje v zaporedju izračuna."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:361
msgid ""
"In our case, we created a 5% environmental tax (Ecotax) and put it *before* "
"the Belgian base tax of 21%."
msgstr ""
"V našem primeru smo ustvarili 5% okoljski davek (Ecotax) in ga postavili "
"*pred* belgijski osnovni davek 21%."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:0
msgid "Environmental tax sequence in Belgium."
msgstr "Zaporedje okoljskega davka v Belgiji."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:368
msgid ":doc:`taxes/tax_computation`"
msgstr ":doc:`taxes/tax_computation`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:369
msgid ":doc:`taxes/fiscal_positions`"
msgstr ":doc:`taxes/fiscal_positions`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:370
msgid ":doc:`taxes/B2B_B2C`"
msgstr ":doc:`taxes/B2B_B2C`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:371
msgid ":doc:`reporting/tax_returns`"
msgstr ":doc:`reporting/tax_returns`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:3
msgid "B2B (tax excluded) and B2C (tax included) pricing"
msgstr "Cene B2B (brez davka) in B2C (z davkom)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:5
msgid ""
"When working with consumers, prices are usually expressed with taxes "
"included in the price (e.g., in most eCommerce). But, when you work in a B2B "
"environment, companies usually negotiate prices with taxes excluded."
msgstr ""
"Pri delu s potrošniki so cene običajno izražene z davki, vključenimi v ceno "
"(npr. pri večini e-trgovine). Toda ko delate v B2B okolju, podjetja običajno "
"pogajajo o cenah brez davkov."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:9
msgid ""
"Odoo manages both use cases easily, as long as you register your prices on "
"the product with taxes excluded or included, but not both together. If you "
"manage all your prices with tax included (or excluded) only, you can still "
"easily do sales order with a price having taxes excluded (or included) : "
"that's easy."
msgstr ""
"Odoo enostavno upravlja oba primera uporabe, če registrirate svoje cene na "
"izdelku z davki izključenimi ali vključenimi, vendar ne obojega skupaj. Če "
"upravljate vse svoje cene z vključenim davkom (ali izključenim), lahko še "
"vedno enostavno naredite prodajni nalog s ceno, ki ima davke izključene (ali "
"vključene): to je enostavno."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:14
msgid ""
"This documentation is only for the specific use case where you need to have "
"two references for the price (tax included or excluded), for the same "
"product. The reason of the complexity is that there is not a symmetrical "
"relationship with prices included and prices excluded, as shown in this use "
"case, in Belgium with a tax of 21%:"
msgstr ""
"Ta dokumentacija je samo za poseben primer uporabe, ko potrebujete dve "
"referenci za ceno (z davkom ali brez), za isti izdelek. Razlog za "
"zapletenost je, da ni simetričnega razmerja med cenami z vključenimi in "
"cenami z izključenimi davki, kot je prikazano v tem primeru uporabe v "
"Belgiji z davkom 21%:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:19
msgid "Your eCommerce has a product at **10€ (taxes included)**"
msgstr "Vaša spletna trgovina ima izdelek po **10 € (vključno z davki)**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:21
msgid "This would do **8.26€ (taxes excluded)** and a **tax of 1.74€**"
msgstr "To bi znašalo **8,26 € (brez davkov)** in **davek v višini 1,74 €**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:23
msgid ""
"But for the same use case, if you register the price without taxes on the "
"product form (8.26€), you get a price with tax included at 9.99€, because:"
msgstr ""
"Toda za isti primer uporabe, če v obrazcu izdelka vnesete ceno brez davkov "
"(8,26 €), dobite ceno z vključenim davkom 9,99 €, ker:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:26
msgid "**8.26€ \\* 1.21 = 9.99€**"
msgstr "**8,26 € \\* 1,21 = 9,99 €**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:28
msgid ""
"So, depending on how you register your prices on the product form, you will "
"have different results for the price including taxes and the price excluding "
"taxes:"
msgstr ""
"Torej, odvisno od tega, kako vnesete cene v obrazcu izdelka, boste dobili "
"različne rezultate za ceno z vključenimi davki in ceno brez davkov:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:31
msgid "Taxes Excluded: **8.26€ & 10.00€**"
msgstr "Brez davkov: **8,26 € in 10,00 €**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:33
msgid "Taxes Included: **8.26€ & 9.99€**"
msgstr "Z vključenimi davki: **8,26 € in 9,99 €**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:36
msgid ""
"If you buy 100 pieces at 10€ taxes included, it gets even more tricky. You "
"will get: **1000€ (taxes included) = 826.45€ (price) + 173.55€ (taxes)** "
"Which is very different from a price per piece at 8.26€ tax excluded."
msgstr ""
"Če kupite 100 kosov po 10 € z vključenimi davki, postane še bolj zapleteno. "
"Dobili boste: **1000 € (z vključenimi davki) = 826,45 € (cena) + 173,55 € "
"(davki)** Kar se zelo razlikuje od cene na kos 8,26 € brez davka."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:40
msgid ""
"This documentation explains how to handle the very specific use case where "
"you need to handle the two prices (tax excluded and included) on the product "
"form within the same company."
msgstr ""
"Ta dokumentacija pojasnjuje, kako obravnavati zelo poseben primer uporabe, "
"kjer morate v istem podjetju v obrazcu izdelka upravljati obe ceni (brez "
"davka in z vključenim davkom)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:44
msgid ""
"In terms of finance, you have no more revenues selling your product at 10€ "
"instead of 9.99€ (for a 21% tax), because your revenue will be exactly the "
"same at 9.99€, only the tax is 0.01€ higher. So, if you run an eCommerce in "
"Belgium, make your customer a favor and set your price at 9.99€ instead of "
"10€. Please note that this does not apply to 20€ or 30€, or other tax rates, "
"or a quantity >1. You will also make you a favor since you can manage "
"everything tax excluded, which is less error prone and easier for your "
"salespeople."
msgstr ""
"Z vidika financ nimate več prihodkov, če izdelek prodajate po 10 € namesto "
"9,99 € (za 21-odstotni davek), ker bo vaš prihodek natanko enak pri 9,99 €, "
"le davek bo za 0,01 € višji. Torej, če vodite spletno trgovino v Belgiji, "
"naredite stranki uslugo in nastavite ceno na 9,99 € namesto 10 €. "
"Upoštevajte, da to ne velja za 20 € ali 30 € ali druge davčne stopnje ali "
"količino >1. S tem boste naredili tudi sebi uslugo, saj lahko vse upravljate "
"brez davkov, kar je manj nagnjeno k napakam in lažje za vaše prodajalce."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:55
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/guatemala.rst:12
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/uruguay.rst:12
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvodna predstavitev"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:57
msgid ""
"The best way to avoid this complexity is to choose only one way of managing "
"your prices and stick to it: price without taxes or price with taxes "
"included. Define which one is the default stored on the product form (on the "
"default tax related to the product), and let Odoo compute the other one "
"automatically, based on the pricelist and fiscal position. Negotiate your "
"contracts with customers accordingly. This perfectly works out-of-the-box "
"and you have no specific configuration to do."
msgstr ""
"Najboljši način, da se izognete tej zapletenosti, je, da izberete le en "
"način upravljanja cen in se ga držite: cena brez davkov ali cena z "
"vključenimi davki. Določite, katera je privzeta, shranjena v obrazcu izdelka "
"(v privzetem davku, povezanem z izdelkom), in pustite Odoo, da drugi način "
"samodejno izračuna na podlagi cenika in davčnega položaja. Pogodbe s "
"strankami pogajajte ustrezno. To popolnoma deluje takoj po namestitvi in ne "
"potrebujete nobene posebne konfiguracije."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:63
msgid ""
"If you can not do that and if you really negotiate some prices with tax "
"excluded and, for other customers, others prices with tax included, you must:"
msgstr ""
"Če tega ne morete storiti in če resnično pogajate nekatere cene brez davka "
"in za druge stranke druge cene z vključenim davkom, morate:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:66
msgid ""
"always store the default price **tax excluded** on the product form, and "
"apply a tax (price excluded on the product form)"
msgstr ""
"v obrazcu izdelka vedno shraniti privzeto ceno **brez davka** in uporabiti "
"davek (cena brez davka v obrazcu izdelka)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:69
msgid ""
"create a pricelist with prices in **tax included**, for specific customers"
msgstr "ustvariti cenik s cenami **z vključenimi davki** za določene stranke"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:71
msgid ""
"create a fiscal position that switches the tax excluded to a tax included"
msgstr ""
"ustvariti davčni položaj, ki preklopi davek brez vključenih davkov na davek "
"z vključenimi davki"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:73
msgid ""
"assign both the pricelist and the fiscal position to customers who want to "
"benefit to this pricelist and fiscal position"
msgstr ""
"dodeliti tako cenik kot davčni položaj strankam, ki želijo imeti koristi od "
"tega cenika in davčnega položaja"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:76
msgid "For the purpose of this documentation, we will use the above use case:"
msgstr "Za namene te dokumentacije bomo uporabili zgornji primer uporabe:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:78
msgid "your product default sale price is 8.26€ tax excluded"
msgstr "privzeta prodajna cena vašega izdelka je 8,26 € brez davka"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:80
msgid ""
"but we want to sell it at 10€, tax included, in our shops or eCommerce "
"website"
msgstr ""
"vendar ga želimo prodajati po 10 € z vključenim davkom v naših trgovinah ali "
"na spletni strani e-trgovine"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:83
msgid "Setting your products"
msgstr "Nastavitev vaših izdelkov"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:85
msgid ""
"Your company must be configured with tax excluded by default. This is "
"usually the default configuration, but you can check your **Default Sale "
"Tax** from the menu :menuselection:`Configuration --> Settings` of the "
"Accounting application."
msgstr ""
"Vaše podjetje mora biti privzeto konfigurirano z davkom, ki ni vključen. To "
"je običajno privzeta konfiguracija, vendar lahko preverite svoj **Privzeti "
"prodajni davek** v meniju :menuselection:`Konfiguracija --> Nastavitve` "
"aplikacije Računovodstvo."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:92
msgid ""
"Once done, you can create a **B2C** pricelist. You can activate the "
"pricelist feature per customer from the menu: :menuselection:`Configuration "
"--> Settings` of the Sale application. Choose the option **different prices "
"per customer segment**."
msgstr ""
"Ko končate, lahko ustvarite cenovno listo **B2C**. Funkcijo cenikov lahko "
"aktivirate za vsakega kupca v meniju: :menuselection:`Konfiguracija --> "
"Nastavitve` aplikacije Prodaja. Izberite možnost **različne cene za "
"posamezen segment kupcev**."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:96
msgid ""
"Once done, create a B2C pricelist from the "
"menu :menuselection:`Configuration --> Pricelists`. It's also good to rename "
"the default pricelist into B2B to avoid confusion."
msgstr ""
"Ko končate, ustvarite cenovno listo B2C v meniju "
":menuselection:`Konfiguracija --> Ceniki`. Dobro je tudi preimenovati "
"privzeti cenik v B2B, da se izognete zmedi."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:99
msgid ""
"Then, create a product at 8.26€, with a tax of 21% (defined as tax not "
"included in price) and set a price on this product for B2C customers at 10€, "
"from the :menuselection:`Sales --> Products` menu of the Sales application:"
msgstr ""
"Nato ustvarite izdelek po ceni 8,26 €, z davkom 21 % (definiran kot davek, "
"ki ni vključen v ceno) in nastavite ceno tega izdelka za kupce B2C na 10 €, "
"v meniju :menuselection:`Prodaja --> Izdelki` aplikacije Prodaja:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:107
msgid "Setting the B2C fiscal position"
msgstr "Nastavitev davčnega položaja B2C"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:109
msgid ""
"From the accounting application, create a B2C fiscal position from this "
"menu: :menuselection:`Configuration --> Fiscal Positions`. This fiscal "
"position should map the VAT 21% (tax excluded of price) with a VAT 21% (tax "
"included in price)"
msgstr ""
"V aplikaciji računovodstva ustvarite davčni položaj B2C v tem meniju: "
":menuselection:`Konfiguracija --> Davčni položaji`. Ta davčni položaj naj "
"preslika DDV 21 % (davek ni vključen v ceno) z DDV 21 % (davek vključen v "
"ceno)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:117
msgid "Test by creating a quotation"
msgstr "Preskus z ustvarjanjem ponudbe"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:119
msgid ""
"Create a quotation from the Sale application, using "
"the :menuselection:`Sales --> Quotations` menu. You should have the "
"following result: 8.26€ + 1.73€ = 9.99€."
msgstr ""
"Ustvarite ponudbo v aplikaciji Prodaja, z uporabo menija "
":menuselection:`Prodaja --> Ponudbe`. Dobiti morate naslednji rezultat: 8,26 "
"€ + 1,73 € = 9,99 €."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:125
msgid ""
"Then, create a quotation but **change the pricelist to B2C and the fiscal "
"position to B2C** on the quotation, before adding your product. You should "
"have the expected result, which is a total price of 10€ for the customer: "
"8.26€ + 1.74€ = 10.00€."
msgstr ""
"Nato ustvarite ponudbo, vendar **spremenite cenik v B2C in davčni položaj v "
"B2C** na ponudbi, preden dodate svoj izdelek. Dobiti morate pričakovani "
"rezultat, ki je skupna cena 10 € za kupca: 8,26 € + 1,74 € = 10,00 €."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:132
msgid "This is the expected behavior for a customer of your shop."
msgstr "To je pričakovano obnašanje za kupca v vaši trgovini."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:135
msgid "Avoid changing every sale order"
msgstr "Izogibanje spreminjanju vsakega prodajnega naloga"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:137
msgid ""
"If you negotiate a contract with a customer, whether you negotiate tax "
"included or tax excluded, you can set the pricelist and the fiscal position "
"on the customer form so that it will be applied automatically at every sale "
"of this customer."
msgstr ""
"Če pogajate pogodbo s kupcem, ne glede na to, ali se pogajate z davkom "
"vključenim ali z davkom izključenim, lahko nastavite cenik in davčni položaj "
"v obrazcu kupca, tako da se bo samodejno uporabljal pri vsaki prodaji temu "
"kupcu."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:141
msgid ""
"The pricelist is in the **Sales & Purchases** tab of the customer form, and "
"the fiscal position is in the accounting tab."
msgstr ""
"Cenik se nahaja v zavihku **Prodaja in nabava** obrazca kupca, davčni "
"položaj pa v zavihku računovodstva."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:144
msgid ""
"Note that this is error prone: if you set a fiscal position with tax "
"included in prices but use a pricelist that is not included, you might have "
"wrong prices calculated for you. That's why we usually recommend companies "
"to only work with one price reference."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da je to nagnjeno k napakam: če nastavite davčni položaj z "
"davkom vključenim v cene, vendar uporabite cenik, ki ni vključen, lahko "
"znesek cen napačno izračunan. Zato običajno priporočamo podjetjem, da delajo "
"samo z eno cenovno referenco."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:5
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/brazil.rst:186
msgid "AvaTax integration"
msgstr "Integracija AvaTax"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:7
msgid ""
"Avalara's *AvaTax* is a cloud-based tax software. Integrating *AvaTax* with "
"Odoo provides real-time and region-specific tax calculations when users "
"sell, purchase, and invoice items in Odoo. *AvaTax* tax calculation is "
"supported with every United Nations charted country, including inter-border "
"transactions."
msgstr ""
"Avalarov *AvaTax* je oblačna programska oprema za davke. Integracija "
"*AvaTax* z Odoo zagotavlja izračune davkov v realnem času in specifične za "
"regijo, ko uporabniki prodajajo, kupujejo in izdajajo račune za postavke v "
"Odoo. Izračun davka *AvaTax* je podprt v vseh državah, ki so opredeljene v "
"Združenih narodih, vključno s čezmejnimi transakcijami."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:13
msgid ""
"*AvaTax* is only available for integration with databases/companies that "
"have locations in the United States, Canada, and Brazil. This means the "
"fiscal position/country of a database can only be set to the United States, "
"Canada, or Brazil. For more information, reference this "
"documentation: :ref:`accounting/avatax/fiscal_country`."
msgstr ""
"*AvaTax* je na voljo za integracijo samo z bazami podatkov/podjetji, ki "
"imajo lokacije v Združenih državah Amerike, Kanadi in Braziliji. To pomeni, "
"da je lahko davčni položaj/država baze podatkov nastavljen samo na Združene "
"države Amerike, Kanado ali Brazilijo. Za več informacij glejte to "
"dokumentacijo: :ref:`accounting/avatax/fiscal_country`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:18
msgid ""
"*AvaTax* accounts for location-based tax rates for each state, county, and "
"city. It improves remittance accuracy by paying close attention to laws, "
"rules, jurisdiction boundaries, and special circumstances (like, tax "
"holidays, and product exemptions). Companies who integrate with *AvaTax* can "
"maintain control of tax-calculations in-house with this simple :abbr:`API "
"(application programming interface)` integration."
msgstr ""
"*AvaTax* upošteva davčne stopnje, ki temeljijo na lokaciji, za vsako zvezno "
"državo, okrožje in mesto. Izboljša natančnost nakazil s pozornim "
"spremljanjem zakonov, pravil, meja pristojnosti in posebnih okoliščin (kot "
"so davčni prazniki in oprostitve izdelkov). Podjetja, ki se integrirajo z "
"*AvaTax*, lahko ohranijo nadzor nad izračuni davkov interno s to preprosto "
"integracijo :abbr:`API (programski vmesnik aplikacije)`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:25
msgid "Some limitations exist in Odoo while using AvaTax for tax calculation:"
msgstr "V Odoo obstajajo nekatere omejitve pri uporabi AvaTax za izračun davka:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:27
msgid ""
"AvaTax uses the company address by default. To use the warehouse address, "
"enable :ref:`Allow Ship Later <pos/shop/ship>` in the **POS** app settings."
msgstr ""
"AvaTax privzeto uporablja naslov podjetja. Če želite uporabiti naslov "
"skladišča, omogočite :ref:`Dovoli poznejšo pošiljko <pos/shop/ship>` v "
"nastavitvah aplikacije **POS**."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:29
msgid ""
"Excise tax is **not** supported. This includes tobacco/vape taxes, fuel "
"taxes, and other specific industries."
msgstr ""
"Trošarina **ni** podprta. To vključuje davke na tobak/elektronske cigarete, "
"davke na gorivo in druge specifične panoge."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:33
msgid ""
"Avalara's support documents: `About AvaTax <https://community.avalara.com/"
"support/s/document-item?language=en_US>`_"
msgstr ""
"Dokumenti podpore Avalara: `O sistemu AvaTax <https://community.avalara.com/"
"support/s/document-item?language=en_US>`_"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:37
msgid "Set up on AvaTax"
msgstr "Nastavitev v sistemu AvaTax"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:39
msgid ""
"To use *AvaTax*, an account with Avalara is required for the setup. If one "
"has not been set up yet, connect with Avalara to purchase a license: "
"`Avalara: Let's Talk <https://www.avalara.com/us/en/get-started.html?"
"campaignID=701Uz00000kcMwLIAU&utm_campaign=AMER_PROS_Unpaid-Synd_General-"
"Contact_07_2025_ODOO-Page---Contact-"
"Us&marketing_channel=web_referral&vendor=partner&paid_unpaid=unpaid&target_audience=prospect>`_."
msgstr ""
"Za uporabo *AvaTax* je za nastavitev potreben račun pri Avalari. Če še ni "
"bil nastavljen, se povežite z Avalaro za nakup licence: `Avalara: Let's Talk "
"<https://www.avalara.com/us/en/get-"
"started.html?campaignID=701Uz00000kcMwLIAU&utm_campaign=AMER_PROS_Unpaid-"
"Synd_General-Contact_07_2025_ODOO-Page---Contact-"
"Us&marketing_channel=web_referral&vendor=partner&paid_unpaid=unpaid&target_audience=prospect>"
"`_."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:44
msgid ""
"Upon account setup, take note of the *AvaTax* :guilabel:`Account ID`. This "
"will be needed in the :ref:`Odoo setup <accounting/avatax/credentials>`. In "
"Odoo, this number is the :guilabel:`API ID`."
msgstr ""
"Pri nastavitvi računa si zabeležite :guilabel:`ID računa` *AvaTax*. To bo "
"potrebno pri :ref:`nastavitvi Odoo <accounting/avatax/credentials>`. V Odoo "
"je ta številka :guilabel:`ID za API`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:48
msgid "Then, `create a basic company profile <https://www.odoo.com/r/2k0>`_."
msgstr "Nato `ustvarite osnovni profil podjetja <https://www.odoo.com/r/2k0>`_."

