msgstr "Podrobnosti CSC"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/brazil.rst:676
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration --> Settings` and scroll "
"to the :guilabel:`Taxes` section. In the :guilabel:`NFC-e configuration` "
"section, complete the following CSC (Taxpayer Security Code) fields:"
msgstr ""
"Pojdite na :menuselection:`Računovodstvo --> Konfiguracija --> Nastavitve` "
"in se pomaknite do razdelka :guilabel:`Davki`. V razdelku "
":guilabel:`Konfiguracija NFC-e` izpolnite naslednja polja CSC (varnostna "
"koda davčnega zavezanca):"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/brazil.rst:680
msgid ""
":guilabel:`CSC ID`: The *CSC ID* or *CSC Token* is an identification of the "
"taxpayer security code, which can have 1 to 6 digits and is available on the "
"official website of your state’s Department of Finance (SEFAZ)."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`ID CSC`: *ID CSC* ali *žeton CSC* je identifikacija varnostne "
"kode davčnega zavezanca, ki ima lahko od 1 do 6 števk in je na voljo na "
"uradni spletni strani finančnega ministrstva vaše države (SEFAZ)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/brazil.rst:683
msgid ""
":guilabel:`CSC Number`: The *CSC Number* is a code of up to 36 characters "
"that only you and the Department of Finance know. It is used to generate the "
"QR Code of the NFC-e and ensure the authenticity of the DANFE."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Številka CSC`: *Številka CSC* je koda do 36 znakov, ki jo poznata "
"le vi in finančno ministrstvo. Uporablja se za generiranje QR kode NFC-e in "
"zagotavljanje pristnosti DANFE."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/brazil.rst:688
msgid ""
"The information required for these fields can be generated through the SEFAZ "
"website of each Brazilian State by the company's accountant."
msgstr ""
"Podatke, potrebne za ta polja, lahko generira računovodja podjetja prek "
"spletne strani SEFAZ posamezne brazilske države."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/brazil.rst:696
